*1. Add Hermes to `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`*

```
{
  agents: {
    defaults: {
      model: { primary: "eastrouter/moonshotai/kimi-k2.7-code" },
      workspace: "C:\\Users\\Chaman\\.openclaw\\workspace"
    },
    list: [
      {
        id: "hermes",
        default: true,
        model: { primary: "xai/grok-4.3" },
        instructions: {
          role: "project_manager",
          description: "You are Hermes, the planning brain. Do not write code. Analyze requests, break them into tasks, and delegate implementation to the OpenClaw agent. Ask clarifying questions when needed."
        },
        groupChat: {
          mentionPatterns: ["@hermes", "hermes"]
        }
      },
      {
        id: "openclaw",
        model: { primary: "eastrouter/moonshotai/kimi-k2.7-code" },
        instructions: {
          role: "implementation",
          description: "You are OpenClaw, the implementation agent. Never plan or ask Hermes what to do. Receive tasks, write code, run tests, and report results."
        },
        groupChat: {
          mentionPatterns: ["@openclaw", "openclaw"]
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  bindings: [
    { agentId: "hermes", match: { channel: "slack", threadId: "1782502252.806539" } }
  ]
}
```
*2. How the workflow works*

| Step | Who | Action |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | You | Ask Hermes in Slack: `@hermes build a script that reverses a string` |
| 2 | Hermes | Plans and delegates to me via internal tool: `sessions_send(agentId="openclaw", message="...")` |
| 3 | OpenClaw | Writes/runs code and reports back to Hermes |
| 4 | Hermes | Summarizes and replies to you |

*3. The blocker right now*

`<@U0BCRBTEBGE> (Hermes Brain)` appears to be a Slack user/bot account, *not* an OpenClaw agent registered in this gateway. Until Hermes is added to `agents.list`, I can't send him tasks and he can't spawn me as a sub-agent.

Two practical options:

1. *Add Hermes as a configured OpenClaw agent* (recommended) — gives real `@hermes` / `@openclaw` routing.
2. *Keep Hermes outside OpenClaw* — then he needs to post tasks to my Slack thread or call a webhook, and I treat those messages as inbound requests.

Which way do you want to go? If you share the Hermes Brain setup (is it another OpenClaw instance, a custom bot, or a different agent?), I can give you the exact config patch.

